In addition, HPV DNA was detected in two operators
nasal swab specimens; one was positive for HPV 16, and
the other was positive for HPV 58. The HPV subtypes
were consistent with the genotypes detected in the smoke
plume generated by LEEP. These results revealed that
HPV DNA could be transmitted from patients to doctors
through surgical smoke. Thus, surgical smoke produced by
LEEP could lead to HPV infection in surgeons.
